					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I just spent a while whittling the runtime library down to the minimum, and removing that awful NES shell they provide. But my conclusion is that the compiled code is way to inefficient for any useful NES development. Also, if one wants to code a NES-like platform in C, one could just use the guts of a NES emulator and compile as a regular PC executable. It could be made virtually identical to what you'd get with cc65, except you'd have unlimited time per frame, and it wouldn't run on a NES.</div>

